\n;[[BIG Star Entertainment Awards]]\n|{{won|7}}\n|{{nom|0}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|\n;[[Screen Awards]]\n|{{won|11}}\n|{{nom|0}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|\n;[[People's Choice Awards India|People's Choice Awards]]\n|{{won|1}}\n|{{nom|0}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|\n;[[Zee Cine Awards]]\n|{{won|6}}\n|{{nom|7}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"|\n;Other awards, honours and recognitions\n|{{won|140}}\n|{{nom|0}}\n|}\n|- style=\"background-color:#d9e8ff;\"\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''Totals'''\n|-\n| {{won|Wins}}\n| colspan=\"2\" width=50 {{won|240}}\n|-\n|- style=\"background:#d9e8ff;\"\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"font-size: smaller; text-align:center;\" | [[#References|References]]\n|}\n[[Amitabh Bachchan]] ({{IPA-hi|\u0259m\u026a\u02c8ta\u02d0b\u02b1 \u02c8b\u0259tt\u0283\u0259n|IPA}}; born 11 October 1942) is an Indian film actor. He first gained popularity in the early 1970s for movies like ''[[Zanjeer (1973 film)|Zanjeer]]'' and ''[[Deewaar]]'', and was dubbed India's first \"angry young man\" for his on-screen roles in [[Bollywood]]. Referred to as the \"[[Shahanshah|Shahenshah]] of Bollywood\", \"Star of the Millennium\" or \"Big B\",<ref>{{cite web|title=Amitabh Bachchan at 73: An ode to the undisputed 'Shahenshah' of Bollywood|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/amitabh-bachchan-at-72-an-ode-to-the-undisputed-shahenshah-of-bollywood/|publisher=indianexpress.com |accessdate=2015-10-11|date=11 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Rajinikanth reveres Amitabh Bachchan as the 'Emperor of Indian Cinema'!|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/rajinikanth-reveres-amitabh-bachchan-as-the-emperor-of-indian-cinema-hindi-news-144373.html/|publisher= indiaglitz.com |accessdate=2015-10-10|date=10 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/news-archive/print/delhis-date-with-big-b-at-adda-on-friday/|title=Delhi's date with Big B at Adda on Friday|last=|first=|date=27 September 2012|website=|publisher=independent.co.uk|accessdate=2012-09-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Amitabh Bachchan's Big B'day bash: Bollywood came calling |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/india/amitabh-bachchan-s-big-b-day-bash-bollywood-came-calling/story-kXEUI1OtpqOkB1AqTvlKoM.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160724082236/http://www.hindustantimes.com/india/amitabh-bachchan-s-big-b-day-bash-bollywood-came-calling/story-kXEUI1OtpqOkB1AqTvlKoM.html |url-status=live |archive-date=24 July 2016 |publisher=hindustantimes.com |accessdate=2012-10-12 |date=12 October 2012 }}</ref>\nhe has since appeared in over 180 Indian films in a career spanning more than four decades.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://guru.bafta.org/amitabh-bachchan-interview-video |title=Amitabh Bachchan: A Life in Pictures |publisher=Bafta.org |accessdate=23 March 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111228221416/http://guru.bafta.org/amitabh-bachchan-interview-video |archivedate=28 December 2011 }}</ref><ref name=angryyoungman>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/1945451.stm |title=Film legend promotes Bollywood |publisher=BBC News |date=23 April 2002 |accessdate=15 January 2010}}</ref> Bachchan is widely regarded as one of the greatest and most influential actors in the history of [[Indian cinema]].<ref>{{cite web|title= Amitabh Bachchan: Meet the biggest movie star in the world|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/news/amitabh-bachchan-the-biggest-film-star-in-the-world-10034826.html/|publisher= independent.co.uk |accessdate=2015-02-09|date=9 February 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title= Why Amitabh Bachchan is more than a superstar |url= https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-19893525 |publisher= bbc.com |accessdate=2012-10-11|date=11 October 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Wajihuddin|first=Mohammed|title=Egypt's Amitabh Bachchan mania|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2005-12-02/india/27839664_1_bachchan-fan-mania-indians|accessdate=22 November 2011|newspaper=[[The Times of India]]|date=2 December 2005|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130501071157/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2005-12-02/india/27839664_1_bachchan-fan-mania-indians|archive-date=1 May 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Jatras|first=Todd|title=India's Celebrity Film Stars|url=https://www.forbes.com/2001/03/09/0309bollywood.html|work=Article|publisher=[[Forbes]]|accessdate=22 November 2011|date=9 March 2001}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Bachchan Receives Lifetime Achievement Award at DIFF |url=http://www.khaleejtimes.com/displayarticle.asp?xfile=data/newsmakers/2009/November/newsmakers_November64.xml&section=newsmakers&col= |publisher=Khaleej Times |accessdate=24 November 2011 |date=25 November 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130602182846/http://www.khaleejtimes.com/displayarticle.asp?xfile=data%2Fnewsmakers%2F2009%2FNovember%2Fnewsmakers_November64.xml&section=newsmakers&col= |archivedate= 2 June 2013 |df=dmy }}</ref> So total was his dominance of the movie scene in the 1970s and 1980s that the French director [[Fran\u00e7ois Truffaut]] called him a \"one-man industry.\"<ref>{{cite web| work= China Daily| title= Truffaut labeled Bachchan a one-man industry| url= http://app1.chinadaily.com.cn/star/history/00-07-07/l03-film.html| accessdate= 1 February 2008| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080201030338/http://app1.chinadaily.com.cn/star/history/00-07-07/l03-film.html| archivedate= 1 February 2008| url-status= dead| df= dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-10-10/news-interviews/43032903_1_amitabh-bachchan-saat-hindustani-inquilab/ |archive-url=https://archive.today/20131023150403/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-10-10/news-interviews/43032903_1_amitabh-bachchan-saat-hindustani-inquilab/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=23 October 2013 |title=Amitabh Bachchan: Indira Gandhi helped him get into films |publisher=timesofindia.com |date=10 October 2013 |accessdate=23 October 2013 }}</ref>\n\nBachchan has won '''numerous accolades''' in his career, including four [[National Film Awards]] as [[National Film Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]], [[Dadasaheb Phalke Award]] as lifetime achievement award and many awards at international film festivals and award ceremonies. He has won fifteen [[Filmfare Awards]] and is the most-nominated performer in any major acting category at Filmfare, with 41 nominations overall and also won eleven [[Screen Awards]].\n\nApart from National Film Awards, Filmfare Awards and other competitive awards which Bachchan won for his performances throughout the years, he has been awarded several honours for his achievements in the Indian film industry. In 1991, he became the first artist to receive the, which was established in the name of [[Raj Kapoor]]. Bachchan was crowned as [[Filmfare Special Award|Superstar of the Millennium]] in 2000 at the Filmfare Awards. The [[Government of India]] awarded him with the [[Padma Shri]] in 1984,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://india.gov.in/myindia/padmashri_awards_list1.php?start=1340 |title=Padma Shri Awardees \u2013 Padma Awards \u2013 My India, My Pride \u2013 Know India: National Portal of India |publisher=India.gov.in |date= |accessdate=23 March 2012}}</ref> the [[Padma Bhushan]] in 2001 and the [[Padma Vibhushan]] in 2015. France's highest civilian honour, the Knight of the [[Legion of Honour]], was conferred upon him by the French Government in 2007 for his \"exceptional career in the world of cinema and beyond\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Pandey |first=Geeta |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/south_asia/6306201.stm |title=South Asia &#124; French honour for Bollywood star |publisher=BBC News |date=27 January 2007 |accessdate=2 October 2010}}</ref> In 2011, actor Dilip Kumar blogged that ''[[Black (2005 film)|Black]]'' should have been nominated for an [[Academy Awards|Oscar]]. Kumar added: \"If any Indian actor, in my personal opinion, deserves the world's most coveted award, it is you.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/big-b-overjoyed-to-receive-letter-from-dilip-kumar/888188/ prateek verma |title=Big B overjoyed to receive letter from Dilip Kumar |publisher=indianexpress.com |date=15 December 2011 |accessdate=10 January 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn 1999, Bachchan was voted the \"Greatest Star of stage or screen of the Millennium\" in a [[BBC]] ''Your Millennium'' online poll.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/381017.stm |title=ENTERTAINMENT &#124; Bollywood star tops the poll |publisher=BBC News |date=1 July 1999 |accessdate=2 October 2010| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100910010951/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/381017.stm| archivedate= 10 September 2010 | url-status= live}}</ref> In 2001, he was honoured with the Actor of the Century award at the [[Alexandria International Film Festival]] in Egypt in recognition of his contribution to the world of cinema.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/2001/20010904/world.htm#8 |title=The Tribune, Chandigarh, India \u2013 World |publisher=Tribuneindia.com |date=4 September 2001 |accessdate=2 October 2010}}</ref> Many other honours for his achievements were conferred upon him at several International Film at the 2010 [[Asian Film Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/bollywood/news/2010/amitabh-asian-awards-250310.html |title=Actor Amitabh Bachchan &#124; Lifetime Achievement Award &#124; 4th Asian Awards &#124; Film Paa \u2013 Oneindia Entertainment |publisher=Entertainment.oneindia.in |date=25 March 2010 |accessdate=2 October 2010| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20130524143103/http://entertainment.oneindia.in/bollywood/news/2010/amitabh-asian-awards-250310.html| archivedate=24 May 2013| url-status= live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2003, he was conferred with the Honorary Citizenship of the French town of Deauville.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/07/04/stories/2003070400980100.htm |title='Shahenshah' of Bollywood |publisher=The Hindu |date=4 July 2003 |accessdate=2 October 2010 |location=Chennai, India| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20101014135148/http://hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/07/04/stories/2003070400980100.htm| archivedate= 14 October 2010 | url-status= live}}</ref> In October 2003, he was conferred with the Medal of Honour of Morocco, given to him by King Mohammed at the [[International Film Festival of Marrakech|Marrakech International Film Festival]].<ref name=\"Marrakech\">{{cite web | title=imdb.com| work=Honour for Bachchan at Marrakech festival|url=https://www.imdb.com/Sections/Awards/Marrakech_International_Film_Festival/2003| accessdate=11 March 2007}}</ref><ref name=\"timesofindia.indiatimes.com\">{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Shah-Rukh-gets-Moroccos-medal-of-honour/articleshow/17461608.cms |archive-url=https://archive.today/20130126072156/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Shah-Rukh-gets-Moroccos-medal-of-honour/articleshow/17461608.cms |archive-date=26 January 2013 |work=timesof.com |title=Shah Rukh gets Morocco's medal of honour |date=3 December 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref> In October 2003, [[TIME]] magazine dubbed Bachchan as \"the Undisputed Godfather of [[Bollywood]]\".<ref name=\"Perry\">{{cite news| url=http://www.time.com/time/asia/covers/501031027/int_bachchan.html | work=Time | title=The Legend | date=27 October 2003 | first=Alex | last=Perry}}</ref> In April 2005, The [[Walter Reade Theater]] of Lincoln Center in New York honored Amitabh Bachchan with a special tribute, retrospective\u2014titled \"Amitabh Bachchan: The Biggest Film Star in the World\".<ref name=\"Saltz\">{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2005/04/15/movies/15indi.html?_r=0 |title=A Star the World Over but Almost Unknown Here |publisher=indianexpress.com |date=15 April 2005 |accessdate=7 June 2013 |first=Rachel |last=Saltz}}</ref><ref name=\"thedailybeast.com/newsweek\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/newsweek/2005/04/21/the-biggest-film-star-in-the-world.html |title=The Biggest Film Star in the World|publisher=thedailybeast.com/newsweek |date=21 April 2005 |accessdate=7 June 2013}}</ref> In March 2010, he has been named the list of [[CNN]]'s \"top 25 Asian actors of all time\".<ref name=\"Hindustan Times\">{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Big-B-in-CNN-s-top-25-Asian-actors-list/H1-Article1-515456.aspx |title=Big B in CNN's top 25 Asian actors list |publisher=Hindustan Times |date=2010-03-05 |accessdate=2011-08-04 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111101080219/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Big-B-in-CNN-s-top-25-Asian-actors-list/H1-Article1-515456.aspx |archivedate= 1 November 2011 |df=dmy }}</ref>\n\nIn June 2000, he became the first living Asian to have been modelled in wax at London's Madame Tussauds Wax Museum.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.screenindia.com/news/art-of-cinema-is-a-small-contribution-amitabh-bachchan/441709/ |title=Art of cinema is a small contribution: Amitabh Bachchan |publisher=Screenindia.com |date=1 April 2009 |accessdate=2 October 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090604212708/http://www.screenindia.com/news/art-of-cinema-is-a-small-contribution-amitabh-bachchan/441709 |archivedate= 4 June 2009 }}</ref> Another statue was installed in New York in 2009,<ref>{{cite web|author=Amitabh\u2019s Wax Figure in New York |url=http://whatslatest.com/blog/?tag=amitabh-wax-figure-in-new-york |title=Amitabh Wax figure in New York |publisher=Whatslatest.com |accessdate=2 October 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121202033520/http://whatslatest.com/blog/?tag=amitabh-wax-figure-in-new-york |archivedate=2 December 2012 }}</ref> Hong Kong in 2011,<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article1570825.ece |title= Amitabh's wax statue unveiled at Hong Kong Tussauds |publisher=thehindu.com |date=25 March 2011 |accessdate=11 October 2012 |location=Chennai, India}}</ref> Bangkok in 2011,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.madametussauds.com/Bangkok/en/NewsAndEvents/AmitabhBachchanLaunch.aspx |title=Unveils wax figure of India's all-time superstar: Amitabh Bachchan |publisher=madametussauds.com/Bangkok |date=24 August 2011 |accessdate=12 October 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121114095003/http://www.madametussauds.com/Bangkok/en/NewsAndEvents/AmitabhBachchanLaunch.aspx |archivedate=14 November 2012 |df=dmy }}</ref> Washington, DC in 2012<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.indianexpress.com/news/big-b-srk-aishwaryas-wax-figures-at-washington-tussauds/1040813/ |title= Big B, SRK, Aishwarya's wax figures at Washington Tussauds |publisher= indianexpress.com |date=5 December 2012 |accessdate=5 December 2012}}</ref> and Delhi in 2017.<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">{{cite web|url= http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/amitabh-bachchan-misunderstands-his-wax-statue-at-madam-tussauds-delhi-as-his-photo/articleshow/56517118.cms |title= Amitabh Bachchan misunderstands his wax statue at Madame Tussauds, Delhi as his photo |publisher= timesofindia.indiatimes.com |date=13 January 2017 |accessdate=13 January 2017}}</ref>\n\nHe was honoured with an Honorary Doctorate by the University of Jhansi, India, in 2004,<ref>{{cite news|author=Subhash K Jha, TNN |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/lucknow-times/meet-dr-amitabh-bachchan/articleshow/1733064.cms |title=Meet Dr Amitabh Bachchan! \u2013 The Times of India |publisher=Timesofindia.indiatimes.com |date=11 July 2006 |accessdate=2 October 2010}}</ref> the University of Delhi in 2006,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://in.rediff.com/movies/2006/nov/04look.htm |title=A doctorate for Big B: Rediff.com movies |publisher=In.rediff.com |date=4 November 2006 |accessdate=2 October 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071104071931/http://in.rediff.com/movies/2006/nov/04look.htm |archivedate= 4 November 2007 |df=dmy }}</ref>  the De Montfort University in Leicester, UK, in 2006,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.glamsham.com/movies/scoops/06/jul/20amitabh.asp |title=Dr Amitabh Bachchan takes Leicester by storm \u2013 bollywood news |publisher=glamsham.com |date= |accessdate=2 October 2010}}</ref> the Leeds Metropolitan University in Yorkshire, UK, in 2007,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.apunkachoice.com/scoop/bollywood/20070610-0.html |title=Leeds University honours Bollywood icons : Bollywood News |publisher=ApunKaChoice.Com |date=10 June 2007 |accessdate=2 October 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121011070216/http://www.apunkachoice.com/scoop/bollywood/20070610-0.html |archivedate=11 October 2012 |df=dmy }}</ref> the Queensland University of Technology in Brisbane, Australia, in 2011,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.qut.edu.au/about/news/news?news-id=37476 |title=News |publisher=QUT |date= |accessdate=29 November 2011}}</ref> the Jodhpur National University in 2013.<ref name=\"It\u2019s Now Dr. Amitabh Bachchan\">{{cite web|url=http://businessofcinema.com/photos/photos-amitabh-bachchan-receives-doctorate/107285 |title=It's Now Dr. Amitabh Bachchan |publisher=businessofcinema.com |date=2013-10-01|accessdate=2012-10-29}}</ref><ref name=\"articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com\">{{cite news| url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-09-30/jaipur/42535289_1_capt-cp-krishnan-nair-convocation-big-b | work=Timesofindia | title=Jodhpur university to confer doctorate on Big B| date=29 October 2013}}</ref> and the [[Academy of Arts (Egypt)]], [[Egypt]], in 2015.<ref name=\"indianexpress.com\">{{cite web|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/amitabh-bachchan-gets-honorary-doctorate-from-egypts-academy-of-arts/ |title=Amitabh Bachchan gets Honorary Doctorate from Egypt's Academy of Arts |publisher= indianexpress.com |date=2015-04-01 |accessdate=2015-04-01}}</ref><ref name=\"thehindu.com\">{{cite web|url= http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/amitabh-bachchan-honoured-by-egyptian-academy-of-arts-for-his-acting-career/article7061361.ece |title= Amitabh Bachchan honoured by Egypt's Academy of Arts |publisher= thehindu.com |date=2015-04-02 |accessdate=2015-04-02}}</ref> In 2017, he was honored with the [[International Film Festival of India#Indian Film Personality of the Year|Indian Film Personality of the Year]] consisting of a Silver Peacock Medal, a certificate a [[Civilian award]].\n\nOn 24 September 2019 he was awarded the prestigious Dadasaheb Phalake award for 2018 by government of India.{{citation needed|date=December 2019}}\n\n==Civilian award==\n{{Main|Civilian award}}[[File:The President, Shri Pranab Mukherjee presenting the Padma Vibhushan Award to Shri Amitabh Bachchan, at a Civil Investiture Ceremony, at Rashtrapati Bhavan, in New Delhi on April 08, 2015.jpg|thumb|200px|Bachchan received [[Padma Vibhushan]] award from honourable president [[Pranab Mukherjee|Sri Pranab Mukherjee]] in 2015]]\n* 1984 \u2013 [[Padma Shri]] India's fourth highest civilian award from the Government of India.<ref>http://www.indianexpress.com/news/my-family-is-happy-for-aishwarya-big-b/415391/</ref>\n* 1991 \u2013 Order of [[Afghanistan]] by the President of Afghanistan.<ref>{{cite news|url= http://movies.ndtv.com/bollywood/amitabh-bachchan-on-shooting-khuda-gawah-in-afghanistan-613598|title=Amitabh Bachchan on shooting Khuda Gawah in Afghanistan|publisher= ndtv.com|date=27 August 2013 |accessdate=27 August 2013}}</ref>\n* 2001 \u2013 [[Padma Bhushan]], India's third highest civilian honour from the Government of India.\n* 2007 \u2013 Knight of the [[L\u00e9gion d'honneur|Legion of Honour]], France's highest civilian honour from the Government of France for his \"exceptional career in the world of cinema and beyond\". Describing Bachchan as a \"towering Indian personality\" and the \"number-one actor of Indian cinema\", Ambassador Girard said the award \"brings Bachchan into the international legion of world's greatest artistes\".<ref name=\"Legion of Honour\">{{cite news | title=news.bbc.co.uk| work=Amitabh awarded the Legion of Honour|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/south_asia/6306201.stm| accessdate=11 March 2007 | date=27 January 2007| first=Geeta| last=Pandey}}</ref>\n* 2015 \u2013 [[Padma Vibhushan]], India's second highest civilian honour from the Government of India.\n\n==Honorary Doctorate==\n{{Main|Honorary Doctorate}}\n\n* 2004 \u2013 Honorary Doctorate by the [[Jhansi]] University, India.<ref name=\"Jhansi University\">{{cite news | title=timesofindia.indiatimes.com| work=Jhansi University honours Amitabh Bachchan|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/articleshow/1733064.cms| accessdate=11 March 2007| date=11 July 2006}}</ref>\n* 2006 \u2013 Honorary Doctorate Degree on by his alma mater [[University of Delhi]], India.<ref name=\"Delhi University\">{{cite web|title=in.rediff.com |work=Delhi University honours Bachchan |url=http://in.rediff.com/movies/2006/nov/04look.htm |accessdate=11 March 2007 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071104071931/http://in.rediff.com/movies/2006/nov/04look.htm |archivedate=4 November 2007 }}</ref>\n* 2006 \u2013 Honorary degree of Doctor of Arts by [[De Montfort University]] in Leicester, UK in recognition of his distinguished career in films. He is the first Indian star to be feted by a foreign university.<ref name=\"De Montfort University\">{{cite web | title=educationuk.org| work=Amitabh Bachchan honoured by De Montfort University|url=http://www.educationuk.org/clubukindia/10/india_bollywood.html| accessdate=11 March 2007}}</ref>\n* 2007 \u2013 Honorary degree of Doctor of Arts by The University Brandan Foster by the [[Leeds Metropolitan University]] in Yorkshire, UK.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lmu.ac.uk/internat/region/south_asia/south_asia.htm |accessdate=13 January 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110103040940/http://www.lmu.ac.uk/internat/region/south_asia/south_asia.htm |archivedate=3 January 2011 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://gulfnews.com/news/world/india/leeds-awards-honorary-degrees-to-3-film-veterans-1.183690 |title=Leeds awards honorary degrees to 3 film veterans |publisher=gulfnews |date=2007-06-10 |accessdate=2011-08-04}}</ref>\n* 2011 \u2013 Honorary Doctorate by the [[Queensland University of Technology]] in Brisbane, Australia for his contribution to the world of entertainment.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.qut.edu.au/about/news/news?news-id=37476 |title=News |publisher=QUT |date= |accessdate=2011-11-29}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/bachchan-awarded-honorary-doctorate-in-australia/862664/ | work=Indianexpress | title=Bachchan awarded honorary doctorate in Australia | date=20 October 2011}}</ref>\n* 2013 \u2013 Honorary Doctorate by the [[Jodhpur National University]], India for his exceptional contribution to Indian Cinema.<ref name=\"It\u2019s Now Dr. Amitabh Bachchan\"/><ref name=\"articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com\"/>\n* 2015 \u2013 Honorary Doctorate from the prestigious [[Academy of Arts (Egypt)]] for his contribution to cinema.<ref name=\"indianexpress.com\"/><ref name=\"thehindu.com\"/>\n* 2018 \u2013 Honorary Doctorate from [[Rabindra Bharati University]] for his contribution to cinema.<ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/kolkata-s-rabindra-bharati-university-set-to-honour-amitabh-bachchan-with-honorary-d-litt-degree-1162599-2018-02-06#close-overlay|title=Kolkata's Rabindra Bharati University set to honour Amitabh Bachchan with honorary D Litt degree|publisher= indiatoday.in |date=15 July 2016 |accessdate=6 February 2018}}</ref>\n\n==National Honours==\n{{Main|National Honours Awards}}\n\n[[File:President Ramnath Kovind conferring Dada Saheb Phalke award on Shri Amitabh Bachchan3.jpg|thumb|150px|Bachchan being conferred with [[Dadasaheb Phalke Award]]]]\n\n* 1980 \u2013 [[Awadh Samman]] by the [[Government of Uttar Pradesh]].\n* 1994 \u2013 [[Yash Bharti Award]], [[Uttar Pradesh]]'s highest honour from the Government of Uttar Pradesh.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Big-B-Jaya-Abhishek-request-UP-to-give-their-Rs-50k-monthly-pensions-to-the-poor-and-the-needy/articleshow/49478209.cms|title=Big B, Jaya, Abhishek request UP to give their Rs 50k monthly pensions to \"the poor and the needy\" |publisher=timesofindia.indiatimes.com|date=2015-10-21 |accessdate=2015-10-21}}</ref><ref name=\"Yash Bharati Samman\">{{cite web|title=apunkachoice.com |work=Awarded by Uttar Pradesh |url=http://www.apunkachoice.com/scoop/bollywood/20061112-3.html |accessdate=11 March 2007 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110716162043/http://www.apunkachoice.com/scoop/bollywood/20061112-3.html |archivedate=16 July 2011 }}</ref>\n* 2002 \u2013 \"Dayawati Modi\" Award. This award is among the highest awards in India in the field of Art, Culture and Education.<ref name=\"Dayawati Modi\">{{cite news|publisher=The Hindu|title=National Dayawati Modi Award for Padamsee|url=http://www.hindu.com/2007/11/18/stories/2007111854520800.htm|accessdate=11 March 2007|location=Chennai, India}}</ref>\n* 2002 \u2013 National Kishore Kumar Award by the Government of Madhya Pradesh for excellence in acting and his unparalleled contribution to the film industry.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/2010/10/14/14763/index.html |title=Yash Chopra honoured with prestigious National Kishore Kumar Award |publisher=Bollywoodhungama.com |date=2010-10-14 |accessdate=2011-08-04}}</ref>\n* 2004 \u2013 \"Living Legend\" Award by the Federation of Indian Chamber of Commerce and Industry (FICCI) in recognition of his contribution to the Indian entertainment industry.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/2004/20040328/spectrum/main4.htm |title=The Sunday Tribune \u2013 Spectrum |publisher=Tribuneindia.com |date=2004-03-28 |accessdate=2011-08-04}}</ref>\n* 2005 \u2013 [[Deenanath Mangeshkar]] award for his contribution to films and music.<ref name=\"Deenanath Mangeshkar\">{{cite web|title=indiaexpress.com |work=Madhya Pradesh honours Bachchan |url=http://www.indiaexpress.com/news/entertainment/20050424-2.html |accessdate=11 March 2007 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061016110044/http://www.indiaexpress.com/news/entertainment/20050424-2.html |archivedate=16 October 2006 }}</ref>\n* 2009 \u2013 [[International Indian Film Academy Awards|IIFA]]-FICCI Frames, \"Most Powerful Entertainer of the Decade Award\" for his contribution to Indian cinema.<ref>{{cite web|title=FICCI FRAMES and IIFA honour ten Bollywood stars |url=http://www.businessofcinema.com/news.php?newsid=12071 |accessdate=20 February 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120214185911/http://www.businessofcinema.com/news.php?newsid=12071 |archivedate=14 February 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ww.smashits.com/events/4721/1/FICCI-USIBC-Award-to-Bollywood-Actors.html |title=FICCI-USIBC Award to Bollywood Actors \u2013 Picture 1 \u2013 Bollywood Parties and Event Pictures |publisher=Ww.smashits.com |date=2009-02-18 |accessdate=2011-08-04 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110716235505/http://ww.smashits.com/events/4721/1/FICCI-USIBC-Award-to-Bollywood-Actors.html |archivedate=16 July 2011 }}</ref>\n* 2011 \u2013 \"Abhinaya Chakravarthy\" Award by the President of India Pratibha Patil.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/photos-news/Photos-Cinema/amitabhgetsabhinayachakravarthyaward/Article4.aspx |title=Amitabh Bachchan &#124; Amitabh gets Abhinaya Chakravarthy Award &#124; Photos Cinema |publisher=hindustantimes.com |accessdate=2011-08-04 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121021181620/http://www.hindustantimes.com/photos-news/Photos-Cinema/amitabhgetsabhinayachakravarthyaward/Article4.aspx |archivedate=21 October 2012 }}</ref>\n* 2011 \u2013 \"Maharashtrian of the Year-the Maanbindu\" Award by the President of India Pratibha Patil.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Bollywood/Big-B-gets-Maharashtrian-of-the-Year-award/Article1-785676.aspx |title=Big B gets Maharashtrian of the Year award |publisher=Hindustantimes.com |date=2011-12-22 |accessdate=2011-12-22 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111223044420/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Bollywood/Big-B-gets-Maharashtrian-of-the-Year-award/Article1-785676.aspx |archivedate=23 December 2011 }}</ref>\n* 2011 \u2013 [[NTR National Award]] in recognition of his outstanding contribution toIndian Cinema by the Government of Andhra Pradesh.<ref>{{cite news|url= http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-04-12/news-interviews/38490940_1_amitabh-bachchan-star-attraction-ntr-national-film-award |title= Amitabh Bachchan receives NTR National film award |publisher= timesofindia.indiatimes.com |date=2013-04-12 |accessdate=2013-04-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.indianexpress.com/news/amitabh-bachchan-receives-ntr-film-award/1101414/ |title= Amitabh Bachchan receives NTR Film Award |publisher= indianexpress.com |date=2013-04-12 |accessdate=2013-04-12}}</ref>\n* 2013 \u2013 President of India 'Medallion of Honour' for contribution to 100 Years of Indian Cinema.<ref>{{cite web|last=Yahoo|title=41 legends honoured at centenary celebrations of Indian cinema|url=http://in.omg.yahoo.com/news/41-legends-honoured-centenary-celebrations-indian-cinema-152807765.html}}</ref>\n* 2014 \u2013 [[ANR National Award]]<ref>{{cite news|url= http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Amitabh-Bachchan-to-be-felicitated-with-ANR-award/articleshow/43078941.cms|title= Amitabh Bachchan to be felicitated with ANR award|publisher= timesofindia.indiatimes.com |date=2014-09-21 |accessdate=2014-09-21}}</ref>\n*2019 - Government of India confers [[Dadasaheb Phalke Award]] for the year 2018.\n\n==National Film Awards==\n{{Main|National Film Awards}}[[File:The President, Smt. Pratibha Devisingh Patil presenting the Best Film Actor Award for the year 2005 to Shri Amitabh Bachchan.jpg|thumb|150px|Bachchan in [[53rd National Film Awards]]]]\n[[File:The President, Smt. Pratibha Devisingh Patil presenting the Rajat Kamal Award to Shri Amitabh Bachchan for Best Actor (Film Paa), at the 57th National Film Awards function, in New Delhi on October 22, 2010.jpg|thumb|150px|Bachchan in [[57th National Film Awards]]]]\nThe [[National Film Awards]] is the most prominent film award ceremonies in India. Established in 1954, it is administered by the [[International Film Festival of India]] and the [[Indian government]]'s [[Directorate of Film Festivals]]. The awards are presented by the [[President of India]]. Due to their national scale, they are considered to be the equivalent of the [[Academy Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|title=National Film Awards|url=http://topic.ibnlive.in.com/national-film-award/profile-1871477.html|publisher=CNN-IBN|accessdate=6 April 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150413131823/http://topic.ibnlive.in.com/national-film-award/profile-1871477.html|archivedate=13 April 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Bachchan has received four awards (a record) in the [[National Film Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]] category and [[Dadasaheb Phalke Award]].\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year || Category || Film || Result\n|-\n|[[38th National Film Awards|1990]] ||rowspan=\"4\"| [[National Film Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]] || ''[[Agneepath (1990 film)|Agneepath]]'' || rowspan=\"5\" {{won}}\n|-\n|[[53rd National Film Awards|2005]] || ''[[Black (2005 film)|Black]]''\n|-\n| [[57th National Film Awards|2009]] || ''[[Paa (film)|Paa]]''\n|-\n| [[63rd National Film Awards|2015]] || ''[[Piku]]''<ref name=\"63rdaward\">{{cite web|title=63rd National Film Awards |url=http://dff.nic.in/writereaddata/Winners_of_63rd_NFA_2015.pdf |publisher=[[Directorate of Film Festivals]] |date=28 March 2016 |accessdate=22 April 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160407212456/http://dff.nic.in/writereaddata/Winners_of_63rd_NFA_2015.pdf |archivedate=7 April 2016 }}</ref>\n|-\n|[[66th National Film Awards|2018]]\n|[[Dadasaheb Phalke Award]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/celebrities/story/amitabh-bachchan-to-be-honoured-with-dada-saheb-phalke-award-2019-1602764-2019-09-24|title=Amitabh Bachchan to be honoured with Dada Saheb Phalke award|publisher=[[India Today]]|accessdate=24 September 2019}}</ref>\n|{{n/a}}\n|}\n\n==Asian Film Awards==\n{{Main|Asian Film Awards}}\n'''Winner'''\n* 2010 \u2013 Lifetime Achievement Award during the 4th Asian Film Awards in Hong Kong.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2010/03/24/amitabh-bachchan-bollywood-legend-gets-asia%E2%80%99s-lifetime-achievement-award.html |title=Amitabh Bachchan: Bollywood legend gets Asia's Lifetime Achievement award |publisher=The Jakarta Post |date=2010-03-24 |accessdate=2011-08-04 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110607060608/http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2010/03/24/amitabh-bachchan-bollywood-legend-gets-asia%E2%80%99s-lifetime-achievement-award.html |archivedate=7 June 2011 }}</ref>\n\n==Filmfare Awards==\n{{Main|Filmfare Awards}}\n<br />\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year || Category || Film || Result\n|-\n|1971\n|[[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actor|Best Supporting Actor]]\n|[[Anand (1971 film)|Anand]]\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|1973\n|Best Supporting Actor\n|[[Namak Haraam]]\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|1974\n|[[Filmfare Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]]\n|[[Zanjeer (1973 film)|Zanjeer]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|1976\n|Best Actor Award\n|[[Deewaar]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|1977\n|Best Actor\n|[[Kabhie Kabhie (1976 film)|Kabhie Kabhie]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-