mitabh Bachchan to be given Sayaji Ratna Award, The Times of India, 3-Nov-2018]</ref>\n\n==Madame Tussauds==\n* In June 2000, Bachchan became the first living Asian to have been immortalised in wax at Madame Tussauds London.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.screenindia.com/news/art-of-cinema-is-a-small-contribution-amitabh-bachchan/441709/ |title=Art of cinema is a small contribution: Amitabh Bachchan |publisher=Screenindia.com |date=2009-04-01 |accessdate=2011-08-04 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090604212708/http://www.screenindia.com/news/art-of-cinema-is-a-small-contribution-amitabh-bachchan/441709 |archivedate= 4 June 2009 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.madametussauds.com/London/OurFigures/Bollywoodstars/AmitabhBachchan/Default.aspx |title=Amitabh Bachchan's wax figure at Madame Tussauds London |publisher=Madametussauds.com |date= |accessdate=2011-08-04}}</ref>\n* In May 2009, a lifelike wax figure of Bachchan has been unveiled at the newly launched 'Bollywood Zone' in Madame Tussauds at Times Square in New York.<ref>{{cite web|author=Agencies |url=http://www.apunkachoice.com/scoop/bollywood/big-bs-wax-statue-unveiled-at-madame-tussauds-new-york.html |title=Big B's wax statue unveiled at Madame Tussauds New York \u2013 Bollywood News |publisher=ApunKaChoice.Com |date=2009-05-23 |accessdate=2011-08-04 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120224031209/http://www.apunkachoice.com/scoop/bollywood/big-bs-wax-statue-unveiled-at-madame-tussauds-new-york.html |archivedate=24 February 2012 }}</ref>\n* In March 2011, Bachchan's wax image has been unveiled at the \"World Famous Home of the Famous\" Madame Tussauds Hong Kong.<ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.thehindu.com/arts/cinema/article1570825.ece |title= Amitabh's wax statue unveiled at Hong Kong Tussauds |publisher=thehindu.com |date=2011-03-25 |accessdate=2012-10-11 |location=Chennai, India}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://gulfnews.com/arts-entertainment/celebrity/amitabh-bachchan-is-the-first-bollywood-actor-to-get-a-wax-figure-1.783136 |title= Amitabh Bachchan is the first Bollywood actor to get a wax figure |publisher= gulfnews.com |date=2011-03-27 |accessdate=2012-10-11}}</ref>\n* In August 2011, Bachchan's wax image has been unveiled at Madame Tussauds museum Bangkok.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.madametussauds.com/Bangkok/en/NewsAndEvents/AmitabhBachchanLaunch.aspx |title=Unveils wax figure of India's all-time superstar: Amitabh Bachchan |publisher=madametussauds.com/Bangkok |date=2011-08-24 |accessdate=2012-10-12 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121114095003/http://www.madametussauds.com/Bangkok/en/NewsAndEvents/AmitabhBachchanLaunch.aspx |archivedate=14 November 2012 |df=dmy }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailypakistan.com/NewsDetails/12199/Amitabh-Bachan%E2%80%99s-wax-figure-unveiled-in-Bangkok.aspx |title=Amitabh Bachan's wax figure unveiled in Bangkok |publisher=dailypakistan.com |date=2011-08-24 |accessdate=2012-10-12 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131022031618/http://www.dailypakistan.com/NewsDetails/12199/Amitabh-Bachan%E2%80%99s-wax-figure-unveiled-in-Bangkok.aspx |archivedate=22 October 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.thailandtourismupdate.com/TravelIndustryReleaseInfo/77/162/MADAME-TUSSAUDS-BANGKOK-UNVEILS-WAX-FIGURE-OF-INDIA\u2019S-SUPERSTAR |title= MADAME TUSSAUDS BANGKOK UNVEILS WAX FIGURE OF INDIA'S SUPERSTAR |publisher= thailandtourismupdate.com |date= 2011-09-08 |accessdate= 2012-10-12 |url-status= dead |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20120630152637/http://www.thailandtourismupdate.com/TravelIndustryReleaseInfo/77/162/MADAME-TUSSAUDS-BANGKOK-UNVEILS-WAX-FIGURE-OF-INDIA%E2%80%99S-SUPERSTAR |archivedate= 30 June 2012 |df= dmy-all }}</ref>\n* On 5 December 2012, Bachchan's wax image has been unveiled at Madame Tussauds museum Washington, DC.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://movies.ndtv.com/movie_story.aspx?section=Movies&Id=300783&keyword=bollywood&subcatg=MOVIESINDIA&nid=300783 |title=Amitabh Bachchan, Shah Rukh Khan, Aishwarya Rai join Washington Tussauds |publisher=ndtv.com |date=2012-12-05 |accessdate=2012-12-05 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130111063100/http://movies.ndtv.com/movie_story.aspx?section=Movies&Id=300783&keyword=bollywood&subcatg=MOVIESINDIA&nid=300783 |archivedate=11 January 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.indianexpress.com/news/big-b-srk-aishwaryas-wax-figures-at-washington-tussauds/1040813/ |title= Big B, SRK, Aishwarya's wax figures at Washington Tussauds |publisher= indianexpress.com |date=2012-12-05 |accessdate=2012-12-05}}</ref>\n* On 13 January 2017, Bachchan's wax image has been unveiled at Madame Tussauds museum Delhi.<ref name=\"ReferenceA\"/>\n\n==International honours and recognition==\n* In July 1999, Bachchan was named the \"Greatest Star of stage or screen of the Millennium\" by BBC online poll where he defeated many [[Hollywood]] legends such as [[Alec Guinness]], [[Marlon Brando]], [[Laurence Olivier]] and [[Charlie Chaplin]].<ref>{{cite news| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/entertainment/381017.stm | work=BBC News | title=Bollywood star tops the poll | date=1 July 1999}}</ref>\n* In 2001, he was ranked as the \"Most Powerful Indian Film Star\" by [[Forbes]].<ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.forbes.com/2001/03/09/0309bollywood_print.html |title= India's Celebrity Film Stars |publisher= forbes.com |date=2001-03-09 |accessdate=2012-10-14 |first=Todd |last=Jatras}}</ref>\n* On 10 September 2001 he was awarded the \"Actor of the Century\" award at the [[Alexandria International Film Festival]]. [[Egypt]]ian Minister of Culture [[Farouk Hosni]] presented Bachchan with the award in recognition of his contribution to international cinema.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/2001/20010904/world.htm#8 |title=The Tribune, Chandigarh, India \u2013 World |publisher=Tribuneindia.com |date=2001-09-04 |accessdate=2011-08-04}}</ref>\n* On 14 March 2003, he was conferred with the honorary citizenship of the French town of [[Deauville]] at the fifth edition of the [[Deauville Asian Film Festival|Asian film festival]]. An honour earlier bestowed on only two people, Queen [[Elizabeth II]] and the [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] space hero, [[Yuri Gagarin]].<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/07/04/stories/2003070400980100.htm | location=Chennai, India | work=The Hindu | title='Shahenshah' of Bollywood | date=4 July 2003}}</ref>\n* In October 2003, he was conferred with the Medal of Honour of Morocco, given to him by King Mohammed at the [[International Film Festival of Marrakech|Marrakech International Film Festival]].<ref name=\"Marrakech\"/><ref name=\"timesofindia.indiatimes.com\"/> \n* In October 2003, [[TIME]] magazine dubbed Bachchan as \"the Undisputed Godfather of Bollywood\".<ref name=\"Perry\"/> He was also featured in its list of Bollywood's Brightest Stars.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.time.com/time/asia/photoessays/bollywood/players5.html |work=Time |date=27 October 2003 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081011132013/http://www.time.com/time/asia/photoessays/bollywood/players5.html |archivedate=11 October 2008 }}</ref>\n* In April 2005, The [[Walter Reade Theater]] of [[Lincoln Center]] in [[New York City|New York]] honored Amitabh Bachchan with a special tribute, retrospective\u2014titled \"Amitabh Bachchan: The Biggest Film Star in the World\".<ref name=\"Saltz\"/><ref name=\"thedailybeast.com/newsweek\"/> The tribute also included \"An Evening with Amitabh Bachchan\", a live appearance by Bachchan hosted at the Lincoln Center's Alice Tully Hall.<ref name=\"An Evening with Amitabh Bachchan\">{{cite web| title=iaac.us| work=Join Amitabh Bachchan for the evening| url=http://www.iaac.us/ab_amitabh.htm| accessdate=11 March 2007| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070415233159/http://www.iaac.us/ab_amitabh.htm| archive-date=15 April 2007| url-status=dead}}</ref>\n* He was honoured along with actors and directors from Hollywood at an International Film Festival in Rabat, Morocco.<ref name=\"Joining the ranks\">{{cite news | title=hindu.com| work=Joining the ranks of Hollywood|url=http://www.hindu.com/2003/09/07/stories/2003090701192000.htm| accessdate=11 March 2007| location=Chennai, India| date=7 September 2003}}</ref>\n* In the weekend of 16 and 17 June June 2007, the [[British Academy of Film and Television Arts]] (BAFTA) hosts a Bachchan spectacular retrospective to honour Bachchan's stellar career. The Chairman of BAFTA ended the event by announcing Bachchan as an honorary Life-Time member of BAFTA.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/features/2007/06/27/2800/index.html |title=Amitabh Bachchan on being honoured by BAFTA |publisher=Bollywoodhungama.com |date=2007-06-27 |accessdate=2011-08-04 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111129061410/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/features/2007/06/27/2800/index.html |archivedate=29 November 2011 }}</ref>\n* On 22 November 2007 he was honoured by the London Mayor Ken Livingstone with \"The Visit London Special Award for Outstanding Achievement\" for his contribution to Indian cinema in the last 30 years.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zeenews.com/znnew/articles.asp?aid=408976&ssid=1&ssname=Movies%20and%20Theatre&sid=ENT&sname= |accessdate=23 November 2007 }}{{dead link|date=May 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref>\n* On 15 January 2009,  Le Salon du Cinema (Cinema Fair) in Paris paid tribute to Indian Cinema for their new edition, with Bachchan being the guest of honour. He also launched a retrospective of his films.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/news/2009/01/15/12433/index.html |title=Bachchans to attend Le Salon du Cinema in Paris as Big B's films will be screened |publisher=Bollywoodhungama.com |date=2009-01-15 |accessdate=2011-08-04}}</ref>\n* On 31 January 2009, he was honoured with the World Economic Forum's Crystal Award at Davos for his contribution to the world of art.<ref>{{cite web|author=Monday, 2 February 2009 at 2337 hrs IST |url=http://www.financialexpress.com/news/wef-honours-amitabh-with-crystal-award/417839/ |title=WEF honours Amitabh with Crystal Award |publisher=Financialexpress.com |date=2009-02-02 |accessdate=2011-08-04}}</ref>\n* In 2009, the Tehran Film Festival has invited Bachchan to receive the Lifetime Achievement Award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tehrantimes.com/index_View.asp?code=185682 |title=Fajr filmfest to honor Amitabh Bachchan |publisher=tehran times |date=2008-12-27 |accessdate=2011-08-04}}</ref>\n* In December 2009, he was honoured with a Lifetime Achievement Award at the Dubai International Film Festival for his outstanding contribution to cinema.<ref>{{cite web|author=Your name |url=http://www.arabianbusiness.com/amitabh-bachchan-wins-lifetime-achievement-award-65881.html |title=Amitabh Bachchan wins lifetime achievement award |publisher=ArabianBusiness.com |accessdate=2011-08-04 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121003013953/http://www.arabianbusiness.com/amitabh-bachchan-wins-lifetime-achievement-award-65881.html |archivedate=3 October 2012 }}</ref>\n* In December 2009, he was honoured with the 8th Asian Film Cultural Award for his contribution to cinema for 40 years.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Big-B-conferred-Asian-Film-Cultural-Award/H1-Article1-484231.aspx |title=Big B conferred Asian Film Cultural Award |publisher=Hindustan Times |date=2009-12-08 |accessdate=2011-08-04 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110606125734/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Big-B-conferred-Asian-Film-Cultural-Award/H1-Article1-484231.aspx |archivedate=6 June 2011 }}</ref>\n* In February 2010, he was honoured with a Lifetime Achievement Award at the Sixth Muscat, Oman International Film Festival (Miff).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.timesofoman.com/echoice.asp?detail=33735 |title=TimesofOman.com |publisher=TimesofOman.com |date=2010-02-19 |accessdate=2011-08-04 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110725231841/http://www.timesofoman.com/echoice.asp?detail=33735 |archivedate=25 July 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.omantribune.com/index.php?page=news&id=66134&heading=News%20in%20Details |title=the edge of knowledge |publisher=Oman Tribune |date= |accessdate=2011-08-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110715002102/http://www.omantribune.com/index.php?page=news&id=66134&heading=News%20in%20Details |archive-date=15 July 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* In March 2010, he has been named the list of CNN's \"top 25 Asian actors of all time\".<ref name=\"Hindustan Times\"/>\n* In March 2010, he has won the Lifetime Achievement Award at the 34th [[Hong Kong International Film Festival]].<ref>{{cite web|title= Amitabh Bachchan Has Won the Lifetime Achievement Award at the 34th HKIFF=http://www.chinesefilms.cn/1/2010/03/18/41s389.htm|publisher= chinesefilms.cn |date=18 March 2010}}</ref>\n* In October 2010, he was honoured with a Lifetime Achievement Award at [[The Asian Awards]] in London.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bollyspice.com/1996/amitabh-bachchan-on-his-lifetime-achievement-award-at-uk-the-asian-awards |title=Amitabh Bachchan on his Lifetime Achievement Award at UK The Asian Awards}}</ref>\n* In April 2012, he was conferred the Polio Eradication Champion award by Rotary International for his invaluable support to the Polio Eradication Programme in India.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.unicef.org/india/media_7645.htm |title= Amitabh Bachchan conferred Polio Eradication Champion award |publisher= unicef.org |date=2012-04-19 |accessdate=2012-10-11}}</ref>\n* In July 2012, he was given the due honor to carry the Olympic torch during the last leg of its relay in London's Southwark.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/amitabh-bachchan-carries-olympic-torch-355100 |title= Amitabh Bachchan Carries Olympic Torch| date= 26 July 2012 | work=The Hollywood Reporter| first=Nyay| last=Bhushan}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://olympicsmedaltally.com/amitabh-bachchan-carries-olympic-torch-in-london.html |title=Amitabh Bachchan carries Olympic torch in London |date=27 July 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121203030918/http://olympicsmedaltally.com/amitabh-bachchan-carries-olympic-torch-in-london.html |archivedate=3 December 2012 }}</ref>\n* In November 2012, he was honoured by the Australian Government for his remarkable contribution to the Indian cinema, which is celebrating its centenary year.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-11-22/news-interviews/35301713_1_amitabh-bachchan-indian-cinema-honour |archive-url=https://archive.today/20130104005545/http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-11-22/news-interviews/35301713_1_amitabh-bachchan-indian-cinema-honour |archive-date= 4 January 2013 |work=timesofindia |title=Amitabh Bachchan felicitated by Australian government |date=22 November 2012 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url= http://www.screenindia.com/news/amitabh-bachchan-honoured-by-australian-government/1035276/ | work= screenindia.com | title= Amitabh Bachchan honoured by Australian government | date= 23 November 2012 | url-status= dead | archiveurl= https://archive.today/20130203025550/http://www.screenindia.com/news/amitabh-bachchan-honoured-by-australian-government/1035276/ | archivedate= 3 February 2013 | df= dmy-all }}</ref>\n* In December 2012, he was honoured with the Tribute to Hindi Cinema Award at the 12th Marrakech International Film Festival.<ref>{{cite news | url= http://iplextra.indiatimes.com/photo/0eHU0zLcyJcOk?q=Morocco | work= timesofindia.com | title= MARRAKECH, MOROCCO | date= 1 December 2012 }}{{dead link|date=September 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.emirates247.com/news-in-images/shah-rukh-big-b-lead-bollywood-marrakech-parade-2012-12-03-1.485688 | work= emirates247.com | title= Shah Rukh, Big B lead Bollywood Marrakech parade | date=3 December 2012}}</ref>\n* On 10 December 2012, he was honoured with the \"Keys to the City of Florence\" at the [[River to River. Florence Indian Film Festival]] in Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Tabloid/Big-B-receives-keys-to-city-of-Florence-feels-honoured/Article1-970935.aspx |title=Big B receives keys to city of Florence, feels honoured |publisher=hindustantimes.com |date=2012-12-10 |accessdate=2012-12-10 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121211014856/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Tabloid/Big-B-receives-keys-to-city-of-Florence-feels-honoured/Article1-970935.aspx |archivedate=11 December 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.indianexpress.com/news/amitabh-bachchan-honoured-at-florence-film-festival/1042343 |title= Amitabh Bachchan honoured at Florence Film festival |publisher= indianexpress.com |date=2012-12-10 |accessdate=2012-12-10}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.bollywoodlife.com/news-gossip/amitabh-bachchan-receives-keys-to-the-city-of-florence-view-pics/ |title= Amitabh Bachchan receives keys to the City of Florence: view pics |publisher= bollywoodlife.com |date=2012-12-10 |accessdate=2012-12-10}}</ref>\n* In May 2013, he will be honoured with \"La Trobe University Global Citizenship Award\" by the [[La Trobe University]] in Melbourne. The University is also introducing a Phd Scholarship called Shri Amitabh Bachchan Scholarship.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Tabloid/Amitabh-Bachchan-to-be-honoured-by-Australian-university/Article1-1049191.aspx |title=Amitabh Bachchan to be honoured by Australian university |date=23 April 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130425180358/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Entertainment/Tabloid/Amitabh-Bachchan-to-be-honoured-by-Australian-university/Article1-1049191.aspx |archivedate=25 April 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.southasiatimes.com.au/news/?p=3554 |title=La Trobe award for Amitabh Bachchan |date=23 April 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130503072758/http://www.southasiatimes.com.au/news/?p=3554 |archivedate=3 May 2013 }}</ref>\n* In May 2013, he will be honoured with \"International Screen Icon\" award by the Victorian Government and the \"Ambassador of Goodwill\" award from the Vice Chancellor of La Trobe University in Melbourne.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://entertainment.in.msn.com/glamsham/article.aspx?cp-documentid=252741635 | title=Amitabh Bachchan to be honoured at Indian Film Festival of Melbourne | date=14 April 2013 | access-date=15 April 2013 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130416172822/http://entertainment.in.msn.com/glamsham/article.aspx?cp-documentid=252741635 | archive-date=16 April 2013 | url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/scholarship-named-after-amitabh-bachchan-in-melbourne/1104367/ | title= Scholarship named after Amitabh Bachchan in Melbourne | date=18 April 2013}}</ref>\n* In September 2013, he was honoured with the \"Global Diversity Award\" in the British Parliament. Speaker of the House of Commons, presented the ornately sculpted glass Award to Bachchan and describing him as \"a Bollywood icon and the most famous Indian film star of all time\".<ref>{{cite news| url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/amitabh-bachchan-presented-with-global-diversity-award-2013/1/309399.html | title= Amitabh Amitabh Bachchan presented with Global Diversity Award 2013| date=12 September 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=http://movies.ndtv.com/bollywood/amitabh-bachchan-to-get-global-diversity-award-417386| title= Amitabh Bachchan to get Global Diversity Award| date=11 September 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Amitabh-Bachchan-to-get-Global-Diversity-Award/articleshow/22483039.cms | title= Amitabh Bachchan to get Global Diversity Award| date=11 September 2013 | work=The Times Of India}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/amitabh-bachchan-to-be-honoured-with-global-diversity-award/1167649/ | title= Amitabh Bachchan to be honoured with Global Diversity Award | date=11 September 2013}}</ref>\n* In March 2014, he was honoured with the \"Global Icon of the Year\" award at the NRI of the Year awards.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-amitabh-bachchan-conferred-global-icon-of-the-year-award-1972140| title= Amitabh Amitabh Bachchan conferred Global Icon of the Year award| date=25 March 2014}}</ref>\n* In May 2014, he was honoured with the \"International Screen Icon\" award during the inaugural awards ceremony at the Indian Film Festival of Melbourne (IFFM).<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.timesofoman.com/News/33278/-Amitabh-Bachchan-honoured-with-International-Screen-Icon-award-at-Indian-Film-Festival-of-Melbourne |title=Amitabh Amitabh Bachchan honoured with International Screen Icon award at Indian Film Festival of Melbourne |date=3 May 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141021131101/http://www.timesofoman.com/News/33278/-Amitabh-Bachchan-honoured-with-International-Screen-Icon-award-at-Indian-Film-Festival-of-Melbourne |archivedate=21 October 2014 }}</ref>\n\n==Other recognition==\n* 2005 \u2013 Ranked as the \"Most popular Star in India\" by the Hansa Research's new syndicated study, Celebrity Track.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/2005/09/11/stories/2005091102480300.htm |title=Bollywood stars score high on Celebrity Track |publisher=The Hindu Business Line |date=2005-09-11 |accessdate=2011-08-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927231836/http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/2005/09/11/stories/2005091102480300.htm