mes.com |date=2013-04-12 |accessdate=2013-04-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.indianexpress.com/news/amitabh-bachchan-receives-ntr-film-award/1101414/ |title= Amitabh Bachchan receives NTR Film Award |publisher= indianexpress.com |date=2013-04-12 |accessdate=2013-04-12}}</ref>\n* 2013 \u2013 President of India 'Medallion of Honour' for contribution to 100 Years of Indian Cinema.<ref>{{cite web|last=Yahoo|title=41 legends honoured at centenary celebrations of Indian cinema|url=http://in.omg.yahoo.com/news/41-legends-honoured-centenary-celebrations-indian-cinema-152807765.html}}</ref>\n* 2014 \u2013 [[ANR National Award]]<ref>{{cite news|url= http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/Amitabh-Bachchan-to-be-felicitated-with-ANR-award/articleshow/43078941.cms|title= Amitabh Bachchan to be felicitated with ANR award|publisher= timesofindia.indiatimes.com |date=2014-09-21 |accessdate=2014-09-21}}</ref>\n*2019 - Government of India confers [[Dadasaheb Phalke Award]] for the year 2018.\n\n==National Film Awards==\n{{Main|National Film Awards}}[[File:The President, Smt. Pratibha Devisingh Patil presenting the Best Film Actor Award for the year 2005 to Shri Amitabh Bachchan.jpg|thumb|150px|Bachchan in [[53rd National Film Awards]]]]\n[[File:The President, Smt. Pratibha Devisingh Patil presenting the Rajat Kamal Award to Shri Amitabh Bachchan for Best Actor (Film Paa), at the 57th National Film Awards function, in New Delhi on October 22, 2010.jpg|thumb|150px|Bachchan in [[57th National Film Awards]]]]\nThe [[National Film Awards]] is the most prominent film award ceremonies in India. Established in 1954, it is administered by the [[International Film Festival of India]] and the [[Indian government]]'s [[Directorate of Film Festivals]]. The awards are presented by the [[President of India]]. Due to their national scale, they are considered to be the equivalent of the [[Academy Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|title=National Film Awards|url=http://topic.ibnlive.in.com/national-film-award/profile-1871477.html|publisher=CNN-IBN|accessdate=6 April 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150413131823/http://topic.ibnlive.in.com/national-film-award/profile-1871477.html|archivedate=13 April 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Bachchan has received four awards (a record) in the [[National Film Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]] category and [[Dadasaheb Phalke Award]].\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year || Category || Film || Result\n|-\n|[[38th National Film Awards|1990]] ||rowspan=\"4\"| [[National Film Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]] || ''[[Agneepath (1990 film)|Agneepath]]'' || rowspan=\"5\" {{won}}\n|-\n|[[53rd National Film Awards|2005]] || ''[[Black (2005 film)|Black]]''\n|-\n| [[57th National Film Awards|2009]] || ''[[Paa (film)|Paa]]''\n|-\n| [[63rd National Film Awards|2015]] || ''[[Piku]]''<ref name=\"63rdaward\">{{cite web|title=63rd National Film Awards |url=http://dff.nic.in/writereaddata/Winners_of_63rd_NFA_2015.pdf |publisher=[[Directorate of Film Festivals]] |date=28 March 2016 |accessdate=22 April 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160407212456/http://dff.nic.in/writereaddata/Winners_of_63rd_NFA_2015.pdf |archivedate=7 April 2016 }}</ref>\n|-\n|[[66th National Film Awards|2018]]\n|[[Dadasaheb Phalke Award]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/celebrities/story/amitabh-bachchan-to-be-honoured-with-dada-saheb-phalke-award-2019-1602764-2019-09-24|title=Amitabh Bachchan to be honoured with Dada Saheb Phalke award|publisher=[[India Today]]|accessdate=24 September 2019}}</ref>\n|{{n/a}}\n|}\n\n==Asian Film Awards==\n{{Main|Asian Film Awards}}\n'''Winner'''\n* 2010 \u2013 Lifetime Achievement Award during the 4th Asian Film Awards in Hong Kong.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2010/03/24/amitabh-bachchan-bollywood-legend-gets-asia%E2%80%99s-lifetime-achievement-award.html |title=Amitabh Bachchan: Bollywood legend gets Asia's Lifetime Achievement award |publisher=The Jakarta Post |date=2010-03-24 |accessdate=2011-08-04 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110607060608/http://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2010/03/24/amitabh-bachchan-bollywood-legend-gets-asia%E2%80%99s-lifetime-achievement-award.html |archivedate=7 June 2011 }}</ref>\n\n==Filmfare Awards==\n{{Main|Filmfare Awards}}\n<br />\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year || Category || Film || Result\n|-\n|1971\n|[[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actor|Best Supporting Actor]]\n|[[Anand (1971 film)|Anand]]\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|1973\n|Best Supporting Actor\n|[[Namak Haraam]]\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|1974\n|[[Filmfare Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]]\n|[[Zanjeer (1973 film)|Zanjeer]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|1976\n|Best Actor Award\n|[[Deewaar]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|1977\n|Best Actor\n|[[Kabhie Kabhie (1976 film)|Kabhie Kabhie]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |1978\n|Best Actor\n|[[Amar Akbar Anthony]]\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|Best Actor\n|[[Adalat (1976 film)|Adalat]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|1979\n|Best Actor\n|[[Don (1978 film)|Don]]\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|1980\n|Best Actor\n|[[Mr. Natwarlal]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|1981\n|Best Actor\n|[[Dostana (1980 film)|Dostanaa]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|1982\n|Best Actor\n|[[Silsila (1981 film)|Silsila]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|1983\n|Best Actor\n|[[Namak Halaal]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|1984\n|Best Supporting Actor\n|[[Andha Kanoon]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|1985\n|Best Actor\n|[[Sharaabi]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|1986\n|Best Actor\n|[[Mard (1985 film)|Mard]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|1989\n|Best Actor\n|[[Shahenshah (1988 film)|Shahenshah]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|1991\n|Best Actor\n|[[Agneepath (1990 film)|Agneepath]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|1991\n|[[Filmfare Lifetime Achievement Award]] (First Recipient)\n|{{N/A}}\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|1992\n|Best Actor\n|[[Hum (film)|Hum]]\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|1993\n|Best Actor\n|[[Khuda Gawah]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|2000\n|Superstar of the Millennium\n|{{N/A}}\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|2001\n|Best Supporting Actor\n|[[Mohabbatein]]\n|{{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2002\n|[